text: Mikhaylovka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Mikhaylovsky Selsoviet, Kharabalinsky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 1,189 as of 2010. There are 14 streets. == Geography == It is located on the Akhtuba River, 42 km north-west from Kharabali. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kharabalinsky District
title: Mikhaylovka, Kharabalinsky District, Astrakhan Oblast
